{{/*
  logrotate config for DragonFly log files (/etc/logrotate.d/dragonfly).
  Go text/template strict (ADR-010). Context: .vars.log_dir (DragonFly, glog -> /var/log/
  dragonfly).

  ★ DragonFly directory ONLY (refactor "sentinel out of destiny redis"): the sentinel
  daemon now deploys destiny `redis` (sentinel_only), and ITS logs are rotated by the
  destiny `redis` logrotate (/var/log/redis). This block covers strictly DragonFly glog.
  (DF logs via glog with its own rotation via --max_log_size - logrotate here cleans up
  what accumulates.)

  copytruncate: DF keeps the log file open and does not react to a log-reopen signal,
  so rotation via copy+truncate (rather than rename+create) is the safe option without
  a restart/HUP. daily + rotate 7: daily rotation, one week retention. compress +
  delaycompress: compression offset by one rotation (the fresh .1 stays uncompressed for
  quick viewing). missingok + notifempty: the log may be absent (service not started) or
  empty - not an error.
*/}}
{{ .vars.log_dir }}/*.log {
  daily
  rotate 7
  size 512M
  copytruncate
  compress
  delaycompress
  missingok
  notifempty
}
